x4freetext: Single and double charged He-3 beams
were accelerated in the Frankfurt 5.5 MV van de Graaff
Self-supporting silicon targets were prepared by vacuum
deposition of natural silicon from carbon boats.
*By authors*.Absorber foils between the target and
detector were used to separate the protons from other
reaction products, especially from the elastically
reaction at 11 MeV incident energy and
Si-28(He3,p)P-30 angular distributions of the p(0)
group at incident energy between 4.3 and 6.3 MeV with
a target thickness of about 40 keV is reported on fig.4
Average compound cross section is reported in table 2.
